President Obama received an update on the severe weather conditions in the Northeast and discussed recovery efforts from Hurricane Sandy. He spoke with officials from the Department of Homeland Security and FEMA about the resources and support being provided to affected states. FEMA continues to deliver essential supplies to distribution points in New York and New Jersey, and additional resources are being pre-positioned. The President was also briefed on emergency housing needs, long-term housing problems, and efforts to restore access to gasoline and electricity. He expressed concern for the safety of those affected by the storm and gratitude for the efforts of first responders, relief workers, and utility crews.